# CSpell Best Practices

## Configuration

- Always use `.cspell.jsonc` for configuration
- Always enable relevant dictionaries for the project (e.g., `de-de` for German, `typescript` for TypeScript)
- CSpell is integrated into ESLint via `@cspell/eslint-plugin` and auto-detects `.cspell.jsonc` configuration
- Restart ESLint server if dictionary changes aren't recognized

## Dictionary Management

- Prefer enabling language-specific dictionaries (`de-de` for German, `es_ES` for Spanish, etc.) over adding common words
- Prefer adding words to the `words` array in `.cspell.jsonc` over disabling checks
- Prefer using regex patterns in `ignoreRegExpList` for common patterns (URLs, selectors, etc.)
- Never add common dictionary words to `words` array - enable the dictionary instead
- Never disable CSpell with comments or for entire files unless absolutely necessary

## When to Add Words

- Do add domain-specific terms (e.g., "thomman", "bddgen")
- Do add technical terms not in standard dictionaries (e.g., "sonarjs")
- Do add brand names and proper nouns
- Don't add common words that exist in language dictionaries - enable the dictionary instead

## Regex Patterns

- Use `ignoreRegExpList` for patterns that appear frequently (e.g., URL patterns, CSS selectors)
- Prefer specific regex patterns over broad ignores
- See `.cspell.jsonc` for actual regex patterns used in the project
